definition.value: The stopping, prevention or reduction of the activity of the enzyme ornithine decarboxylase.
Complex that possesses guanylate cyclase activity and is not bound to a membrane.
A protein complex that forms a transmembrane channel through which potassium ions may cross a cell membrane in response to changes in membrane potential.
Functions in the termination of translation.
Catalysis of the transfer of an acetyl group to a nitrogen atom on the acceptor molecule.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of a phosphodiester to give a phosphomonoester and a free hydroxyl group.
The function that stimulates a cell to grow or proliferate. Most growth factors have other actions besides the induction of cell growth or proliferation.

label.value: imaginal disc growth factor receptor binding

definition.value: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with an imaginal disc growth factor receptor.

Catalysis of the transmembrane transfer of a calcium ion by a voltage-gated channel that is activated in response to light. A voltage-gated channel is a channel whose open state is dependent on the voltage across the membrane in which it is embedded.
A protein complex that forms a transmembrane channel through which calcium ions may cross a cell membrane in response to changes in membrane potential generated in response to a light stimulus.

Membrane associated dimeric protein (240 and 220 kDa) of erythrocytes. Forms a complex with ankyrin, actin and probably other components of the membrane cytoskeleton, so that there is a mesh of proteins underlying the plasma membrane, potentially restricting the lateral mobility of integral proteins.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with any protein component of any cytoskeleton (actin, microtubule, or intermediate filament cytoskeleton).
The binding activity of a molecule that brings together a cytoskeletal protein and one or more other molecules, permitting them to function in a coordinated way.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + H2O -eq- ADP + phosphate -  this reaction requires the presence of single- or double-stranded DNA, and it drives another reaction.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of the epoxide in a juvenile hormone to the corresponding diol.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with 5S ribosomal RNA, the smallest RNA constituent of a ribosome.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the unprocessed 5S ribosomal RNA transcript.
Catalysis of the reaction -  an alcohol + NADP+ -eq- an aldehyde + NADPH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  GDP-L-fucose + beta-D-galactosyl-R -eq- GDP + alpha-L-fucosyl-(1,2)-beta-D-galactosyl-R.
Catalysis of the reaction -  alpha-D-galactose 1-phosphate + UDP-D-glucose -eq- alpha-D-glucose 1-phosphate + UDP-D-galactose.
Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine + beta-D-galactosyl-1,4-N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-R -eq- UDP + N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-1,6-beta-D-galactosyl-1,4-N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-R.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-oxoglutarate + L-histidine -eq- 3-(imidazol-5-yl)pyruvate + L-glutamate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (2S)-2-methylacyl-CoA -eq- (2R)-2-methylacyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine(1+) + nicotinamide -eq- 1-methylnicotinamide + S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine.

Catalysis of the reactions -  peptide-L-methionine + thioredoxin disulfide + H2O -eq- peptide-L-methionine (S)-S-oxide + thioredoxin, and L-methionine + thioredoxin disulfide + H2O -eq- L-methionine (S)-S-oxide + thioredoxin. Can act on oxidized methionine in peptide linkage with specificity for the S enantiomer. Thioredoxin disulfide is the oxidized form of thioredoxin.
Catalysis of the reaction -  6-phospho-D-gluconate + NADP+ -eq- 6-phospho-2-dehydro-D-gluconate + NADPH.
Catalysis of the reaction -  H(2)O + O(2) + sarcosine -eq- formaldehyde + glycine + H(2)O(2).
Catalysis of the reaction -  prostaglandin H(2) -eq- prostaglandin I(2).
Catalysis of the reaction -  sphinganine 1-phosphate -eq- phosphoethanolamine + palmitaldehyde.

Catalysis of the reaction -  CMP-N-acetylneuraminate + beta-D-galactosyl-1,4-N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-glycoprotein -eq- CMP + alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl-2,3-beta-D-galactosyl-1,4-N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-glycoprotein.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + a thiopurine -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + a thiopurine S-methylether.
Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-glucose + N-acylsphingosine -eq- UDP + D-glucosyl-N-acylsphingosine.
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  CoQH2 + 2 ferricytochrome c -eq- CoQ + 2 ferrocytochrome c + 2 H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  cholesterol + NADPH + H+ + O2 -eq- 7-alpha-hydroxycholesterol + NADP+ + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (6R)-6-(L-erythro-1,2-dihydroxypropyl)-5,6,7,8-tetrahydro-4a-hydroxypterin -eq- (6R)-6-(L-erythro-1,2-dihydroxypropyl)-7,8-dihydro-6H-pterin + H(2)O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  an acetic ester + H2O -eq- an alcohol + acetate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  H(+) + O(2) + quercetin -eq- 2-(3,4-dihydroxybenzoyloxy)-4,6-dihydroxybenzoate + CO.
Catalysis of the reaction -  a primary amine + H2O + O2 -eq- an aldehyde + NH3 + hydrogen peroxide.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a transcription factor, any protein required to initiate or regulate transcription.

label.value: translation factor activity, nucleic acid binding

definition.value: Functions during translation by interacting selectively and non-covalently with nucleic acids during polypeptide synthesis at the ribosome.
Catalysis of the reaction -  NADH + H+ + ubiquinone -eq- NAD+ + ubiquinol.

Catalysis of the reactions -  protein serine + H2O -eq- protein serine + phosphate -  protein threonine phosphate + H2O -eq- protein threonine + phosphate -  and protein tyrosine phosphate + H2O -eq- protein tyrosine + phosphate.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a nuclear localization sequence, a specific peptide sequence that acts as a signal to localize the protein within the nucleus.

label.value: cAMP response element binding protein binding

definition.value: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the cAMP response element binding protein.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with oxysterol, an oxidized form of cholesterol.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a sequence of adenylyl residues in an RNA molecule, such as the poly(A) tail, a sequence of adenylyl residues at the 3' end of eukaryotic mRNA.

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a drug, any naturally occurring or synthetic substance, other than a nutrient, that, when administered or applied to an organism, affects the structure or functioning of the organism -  in particular, any such substance used in the diagnosis, prevention, or treatment of disease.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with phenylalkylamine or any of its derivatives.
Catalysis of the transfer of a sulfate group from 3'-phosphoadenosine 5'-phosphosulfate to the hydroxyl group of an acceptor, producing the sulfated derivative and 3'-phosphoadenosine 5'-phosphate.
The action of a molecule that contributes to the structural integrity of bone.
